165
00:11:05.879 --> 00:11:06.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent>He's Bajoran.</c.bg_transparent>

166
00:11:07.179 --> 00:11:12.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent>He's a revered poet, and he wants the job.</c.bg_transparent>
<c.bg_transparent>Besides, Starfleet will be thrilled.</c.bg_transparent>

167
00:11:12.677 --> 00:11:16.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent>They never liked the idea that</c.bg_transparent>
<c.bg_transparent>the Bajorans saw me as a religious figure.</c.bg_transparent>

168
00:11:16.536 --> 00:11:19.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent>How do you know the Bajorans will accept</c.bg_transparent>
<c.bg_transparent>Akorem as their new Emissary?</c.bg_transparent>

169
00:11:19.995 --> 00:11:21.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent>I talked to Vedek Porta.</c.bg_transparent>

170
00:11:21.694 --> 00:11:23.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent>He seems to think that as long</c.bg_transparent>
<c.bg_transparent>as I make it clear</c.bg_transparent>

171
00:11:23.675 --> 00:11:26.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent>that I'm stepping aside</c.bg_transparent>
